#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:45
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Uvod"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:48
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The regular expression editor is an editor for editing regular expression in "
"a graphical style (in contrast to the <acronym>ASCII</acronym> syntax). "
"Traditionally regular expressions have been typed in the <acronym>ASCII</"
"acronym> syntax, which for example looks like <literal>^.*kde\\b</literal>. "
"The major drawbacks of this style are:"
msgstr ""
"Regular expression editor je urednik za uređivanje regularnih izraza u "
"grafičkom stilu (suprotno od <acronym>ASCII</acronym> sintakse). "
"Tradicionalno su regularni izrazi napisani u <acronym>ASCII</acronym> "
"sintaksi, koja na primjer izgleda poput <literal>^.*kde\\b</literal>. Glavni "
"nedostaci tog stila su:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:55
#, no-c-format
msgid "It is hard to understand for non-programmers."
msgstr "Teško je razumljiv za ne-programere."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:58
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It requires that you <emphasis>escape</emphasis> certain symbols (to match a "
"star for example, you need to type <literal>\\*</literal>)."
msgstr ""
"Zahtijeva da <emphasis>zaobiđete</emphasis> određene simbole (da iskoristite "
"zvijezdu na primjer, trebate unijeti <literal>\\*</literal>)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:62
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It requires that you remember rules for <emphasis>precedence</emphasis> "
"(What does <literal>x|y*</literal> match? a single <literal>x</literal> or a "
"number of <literal>y</literal>, <emphasis>OR</emphasis> a number of "
"<literal>x</literal> and <literal>y</literal>'s mixed?)"
msgstr ""
"Zahtijeva da upamtite pravila za <emphasis>prioritet</emphasis> (Šta "
"<literal>x|y*</literal> znači? sami <literal>x</literal> ili broj  "
"<literal>y</literal>, <emphasis>ILI</emphasis> broj <literal>x</literal> i "
"<literal>y</literal> pomiješano?)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:70
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The regular expression editor, on the other hand, lets you <emphasis>draw</"
"emphasis> your regular expression in an unambiguous way. The editor solves "
"at least item two and three above. It might not make regular expressions "
"available for the non-programmers, though only tests by users can tell that. "
"So, if are you a non programmer, who has gained the power of regular "
"expression from this editor, then please <ulink url=\"mailto:blackie@kde.org"
"\">let me know</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Regular expression uređivač, u drugu ruku, dopušta Vam <emphasis>crtanje</"
"emphasis> Vaših regularnih izraza na nedvosmislen način. Uređivač rješava "
"najmanje stavku dva i tri iznad. Možda neće napraviti regularne izraze "
"dostupnim za ne-programere, iako samo testovi korisnika mogu to potvrditi. "
"Dakle, ukoliko niste programer, koji je stekao jako iskustvo na regularnim "
"izrazima ovog uređivača, onda molim <ulink url=\"mailto:blackie@kde.org"
"\">obavijestite me</ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:86
#, no-c-format
msgid "What is a Regular Expression"
msgstr "Šta je Regular Expression"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:88
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A regular expression is a way to specify <emphasis>conditions</emphasis> to "
"be fulfilled for a situation in mind. Normally when you search in a text "
"editor you specify the text to search for <emphasis>literally</emphasis>, "
"using a regular expression, on the other hand, you tell what a given match "
"would look like. Examples of this include <emphasis>I'm searching for the "
"word &kde;, but only at the beginning of the line</emphasis>, or "
"<emphasis>I'm searching for the word <literal>the</literal>, but it must "
"stand on its own</emphasis>, or <emphasis>I'm searching for files starting "
"with the word <literal>test</literal>, followed by a number of digits, for "
"example <literal>test12</literal>, <literal>test107</literal> and "
"<literal>test007</literal></emphasis>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:102
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You build regular expressions from smaller regular expressions, just like "
"you build large Lego toys from smaller subparts. As in the Lego world, there "
"are a number of basic building blocks. In the following I will describe each "
"of these basic building blocks using a number of examples."
msgstr ""
"Regularne izraze gradite na osnovu manjih regularnih izraza, baš kao sto "
"pravite velike Lego igračke od manjih dijelova. Kao u Lego svijetu, postoji "
"broj baznih blokova. Slijedi opis svakog od ovih baznih blokova korištenjem "
"nekoliko primjera."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:109
#, no-c-format
msgid "Searching for normal text."
msgstr "Pretraživanje normalnog teksta."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:110
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you just want to search for a given text, then regular expression is "
"definitely not a good choice. The reason for this is that regular "
"expressions assign special meaning to some characters. This includes the "
"following characters: <literal>.*|$</literal>. Thus if you want to search "
"for the text <literal>kde.</literal> (i.e. the characters <literal>kde</"
"literal> followed by a period), then you would need to specify this as "
"<literal>kde\\.</literal><footnote><para>The regular expression editor "
"solves this problem by taking care of escape rules for you.</para></"
"footnote> Writing <literal>\\.</literal> rather than just <literal>.</"
"literal> is called <emphasis>escaping</emphasis>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:124
#, no-c-format
msgid "Matching &URL;s"
msgstr "Upoređivanje &URL;-ova"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:125
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you select something looking like a &URL; in &kde;, then the program "
"<command>klipper</command> will offer to start <command>konqueror</command> "
"with the selected &URL;."
msgstr ""
"Kada odaberete nešto što izgleda kao &URL; u &kde;, onda će programski "
"<command>klipper</command> ponuditi pokretanje <command>konqueror</command> "
"sa odabranim &URL;-om."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:129
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>Klipper</command> does this by matching the selection against "
"several different regular expressions, when one of the regular expressions "
"matches, the accommodating command will be offered."
msgstr ""
"<command>Klipper</command> ovo radi tako što upoređuje odabrano sa nekoliko "
"različitih regularnih izraza, pa kada jedan od regularnih izraza odgovara, "
"smještajna komanda će biti ponuđena."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:133
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The regular expression for &URL;s says (among other things), that the "
"selection must start with the text <literal>http://</literal>. This is "
"described using regular expressions by prefixing the text <literal>http://</"
"literal> with a hat (the <literal>^</literal> character)."
msgstr ""
"Regular expression za &URL;-ove kaže (između ostalog), da odabir mora početi "
"sa tekstom <literal>http://</literal>. Ovo je opisano koristeći regularne "
"izraze prefiksirajući tekst <literal>http://</literal> sa šeširom "
"(<literal>^</literal> karakter)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:139
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The above is an example of matching positions using regular expressions. "
"Similar, the position <emphasis>end-of-line</emphasis> can be matched using "
"the character <literal>$</literal> (i.e. a dollar sign)."
msgstr ""
"Iznad je primjer upoređivanja pozicija korištenjem regularnih izraza. "
"Slično, pozicije <emphasis>kraj-reda</emphasis> mogu biti upoređene "
"koristeći karakter <literal>$</literal> (i.e. znak dolara)."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:146
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Searching for the word <literal>the</literal>, but not <emphasis>the</"
"emphasis><literal>re</literal>, <literal>brea</literal><emphasis>the</"
"emphasis> or <literal>ano</literal><emphasis>the</emphasis><literal>r</"
"literal>"
msgstr ""
"Pretraživanje riječi <literal>the</literal>, ali ne <emphasis>the</"
"emphasis><literal>re</literal>, <literal>brea</literal><emphasis>the</"
"emphasis> ili <literal>ano</literal><emphasis>the</emphasis><literal>r</"
"literal>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:150
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Two extra position types can be matches in the above way, namely "
"<emphasis>the position at a word boundary</emphasis>, and <emphasis>the "
"position at a <emphasis>non</emphasis>-word boundary</emphasis>. The "
"positions are specified using the text <literal>\\b</literal> (for word-"
"boundary) and <literal>\\B</literal> (for non-word boundary)"
msgstr ""
"Dva posebna tipa pozicije mogu biti upoređena na prethodni način, koji se "
"zove <emphasis>pozicija granice riječi</emphasis>, i <emphasis>pozicija u "
"<emphasis>ne</emphasis>-granice riječi </emphasis>. Pozicije su "
"specificirane koristeći tekst <literal>\\b</literal> (za granicu riječi) i "
"<literal>\\B</literal> (za ne-granicu riječi)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:157
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Thus, searching for the word <literal>the</literal> can be done using the "
"regular expression <literal>\\bthe\\b</literal>. This specifies that we are "
"searching for <literal>the</literal> with no letters on each side of it (i."
"e. with a word boundary on each side)"
msgstr ""
"Prema tome, pretraživanje po riječi <literal>the</literal> može biti "
"obavljeno korištenjem regularnih izraza <literal>\\bthe\\b</literal>. Ovo "
"određuje to da mi tražimo <literal>the</literal> bez slova sa njegove obje "
"strane (i.e. sa granicom riječi sa obje strane)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:162
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The four position matching regular expressions are inserted in the regular "
"expression editor using <link linkend=\"positiontool\">four different "
"positions tool</link>"
msgstr ""
"Četiri regularna izraza za upoređivanje pozicije riječi su smješteni u "
"uređivač regularnih izraza koristeći <link linkend=\"positiontool\">alat za "
"četiri različite pozicije</link>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:168
#, no-c-format
msgid "Searching for either <literal>this</literal> or <literal>that</literal>"
msgstr "Traženje <literal>ovog</literal> ili <literal>onog</literal>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:169
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Imagine that you want to run through your document searching for either the "
"word <literal>this</literal> or the word <literal>that</literal>. With a "
"normal search method you could do this in two sweeps, the first time around, "
"you would search for <literal>this</literal>, and the second time around you "
"would search for <literal>that</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Zamislite da želite proći kroz dokumente tražeći ili riječ <literal>ovo</"
"literal> ili riječ <literal>ono</literal>. Sa normalnom metodom pretrage "
"mogli biste to uraditi u dva poteza, prvi put biste tražili riječ "
"<literal>ovo</literal>, a drugi put riječ <literal>ono</literal>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:176
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using regular expression searches you would search for both in the same "
"sweep. You do this by searching for <literal>this|that</literal>, &ie; "
"separating the two words with a vertical bar."
msgstr ""
"Sa pretragom regularnim izrazima biste tražili obje riječi istovremeno. To "
"možete uraditi tako što pretražujete  <literal>ovo|ono</literal>, &ie; "
"razdvajajući dvije riječi vertikalnim znakom."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:179
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note on each side of the vertical bar is a regular expression, so this "
"feature is not only for searching for two different pieces of text, but for "
"searching for two different regular expressions."
msgstr ""
"Primijetite da je sa obje strane vertikalnog znaka regularni izraz, tako da "
"ova opcija nije samo za traženje dva različita dijela teksta, nego za "
"traženje dva različita regularna izraza."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:184
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the regular expression editor you do not write the vertical bar yourself, "
"but instead select the <link linkend=\"altntool\">alternative tool</link>, "
"and insert the smaller regular expressions above each other."
msgstr ""
"U uređivaču regularnih izraza, Vi ne pišete sami vertikalni znak, nego "
"umjesto toga odaberete <link linkend=\"altntool\">alternativni alat</link>, "
"i umetnete manje regularne izraze jedan iznad drugog."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:190
#, no-c-format
msgid "Matching anything"
msgstr "Upoređivanje bilo čega"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:191
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Regular expressions are often compared to wildcard matching in the shell - "
"that is the capability to specify a number of files using the asterisk. You "
"will most likely recognize wildcard matching from the following examples:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:196
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>ls *.txt</literal> - here <literal>*.txt</literal> is the shell "
"wildcard matching every file ending with the <literal>.txt</literal> "
"extension."
msgstr ""
"<literal>ls *.txt</literal> - ovo <literal>*.txt</literal> je džoker školjke "
"koji predstavlja svaku datoteke koja završava sa <literal>.txt</literal> "
"nastavkom."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:199
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>cat test??.res</literal> - matching every file starting with "
"<literal>test</literal> followed by two arbitrary characters, and finally "
"followed by the test <literal>.res</literal>"
msgstr ""
"<literal>cat test??.res</literal> - pretražuje svaku datoteku koja počinje "
"sa <literal>test</literal> te se nastavlja sa dva proizvoljna znaka, i "
"završava sa <literal>.res</literal>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:205
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the shell the asterisk matches any character any number of times. In "
"other words, the asterisk matches <emphasis>anything</emphasis>. This is "
"written like <literal>.*</literal> with regular expression syntax. The dot "
"matches any single character, &ie; just <emphasis>one</emphasis> character, "
"and the asterisk, says that the regular expression prior to it should be "
"matched any number of times. Together this says any single character any "
"number of times."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:214
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This may seem overly complicated, but when you get the larger picture you "
"will see the power. Let me show you another basic regular expression: "
"<literal>a</literal>. The letter <literal>a</literal> on its own is a "
"regular expression that matches a single letter, namely the letter "
"<literal>a</literal>. If we combine this with the asterisk, &ie; "
"<literal>a*</literal>, then we have a regular expression matching any number "
"of a's."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:222
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"We can combine several regular expression after each other, for example "
"<literal>ba(na)*</literal>. <footnote><para><literal>(na)*</literal> just "
"says that what is inside the parenthesis is repeated any number of times.</"
"para></footnote> Imagine you had typed this regular expression into the "
"search field in a text editor, then you would have found the following words "
"(among others): <literal>ba</literal>, <literal>bana</literal>, "
"<literal>banana</literal>, <literal>bananananananana</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:232
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Given the information above, it hopefully isn't hard for you to write the "
"shell wildcard <literal>test??.res</literal> as a regular expression. "
"Answer: <literal>test..\\.res</literal>. The dot on its own is any "
"character. To match a single dot you must write <literal>\\.</"
"literal><footnote><para>This is called escaping</para></footnote>. In other "
"word, the regular expression <literal>\\.</literal> matches a dot, while a "
"dot on its own matches any character."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:240
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the regular expression editor, a repeated regular expression is created "
"using the <link linkend=\"repeattool\">repeat tool</link>"
msgstr ""
"U uredniku regularnih izraza, ponovljeni regularni izrazi se kreiraju "
"koristeći <link linkend=\"repeattool\">repeat tool</link>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:245
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Replacing <literal>&amp;</literal> with <literal>&amp;amp;</literal> in a "
"&HTML; document"
msgstr ""
"Zamjena <literal>&amp;</literal> sa <literal>&amp;amp;</literal> u &HTML; "
"dokumentu"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:246
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In &HTML; the special character <literal>&amp;</literal> must be written as "
"<literal>&amp;amp;</literal> - this is similar to escaping in regular "
"expressions."
msgstr ""
"U &HTML; specijalni karakter <literal>&amp;</literal> mora biti napisan kao "
"<literal>&amp;amp;</literal> - ovo je slično kao izlazak u regularnim "
"izrazima."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:251
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Imagine that you have written an &HTML; document in a normal editor (e.g. "
"&XEmacs; or &kate;), and you totally forgot about this rule. What you would "
"do when realized your mistake was to replace every occurrences of "
"<literal>&amp;</literal> with <literal>&amp;amp;</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Zamislite da ste napisali &HTML; u normalnom editoru (e.g. &XEmacs; ili "
"&kate;), i da ste totalno zaboravili na ovo pravilo. Šta biste uradili kada "
"biste shvatili da je Vaša greška da ste zamijenili svako pojavljivanje "
"<literal>&amp;</literal> sa <literal>&amp;amp;</literal>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:256
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This can easily be done using normal search and replace, there is, however, "
"one glitch. Imagine that you did remember this rule - <emphasis>just a bit</"
"emphasis> - and did it right in some places. Replacing unconditionally would "
"result in <literal>&amp;amp;</literal> being replaced with <literal>&amp;amp;"
"amp;</literal>"
msgstr ""
"Ovo može biti veoma lako riješeno korištenjem normalne pretrage i izmjene, "
"ali tu postoji, ipak, mala zvrčka. Zamislite da ste se sjetili ovog pravila "
"- <emphasis>pomalo</emphasis> - i uradili to pravilno na nekim mjestima. "
"Bezuvjetna zamjena će rezultovati da<literal>&amp;amp;</literal> bude "
"zamijenjeno sa <literal>&amp;amp;amp;</literal>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:263
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"What you really want to say is that <literal>&amp;</literal> should only be "
"replaced if it is <emphasis>not</emphasis> followed by the letters "
"<literal>amp;</literal>. You can do this using regular expressions using "
"<emphasis>positive lookahead</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"Šta zaista želite reći je da <literal>&amp;</literal> ne bi trebao biti "
"zamijenjen ukoliko <emphasis>nije</emphasis> propraćen slovima <literal>amp;"
"</literal>. Ovo možete učiniti koristeći regularne izraze korištenjem "
"<emphasis>positive lookahead</emphasis>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:268
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The regular expression, which only matches an ampersand if it is not "
"followed by the letters <literal>amp;</literal> looks as follows: "
"<literal>&amp;(?!amp;)</literal>. This is, of course, easier to read using "
"the regular expression editor, where you would use the <link linkend="
"\"lookaheadtools\">lookahead tools</link>."
msgstr ""
"Regularni izrazi, koji se samo podudaraju sa ampersandom ukoliko nije "
"propraćen slovima <literal>amp;</literal> izgleda ovako: <literal>&amp;(?!"
"amp;)</literal>. Ovo je, naravno, lakše pročitati koristeći urednik "
"regularnih izraza, gdje biste koristili <link linkend=\"lookaheadtools"
"\">lookahead tools</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:281
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using the Regular Expression Editor"
msgstr "Korištenje urednika regularnih izraza"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:283
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter will tell you about how the regular expression editor works."
msgstr ""
"Ovaj odlomak će Vam govoriti o tome kako urednik regularnih izraza radi."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:291
#, no-c-format
msgid "The organization of the screen"
msgstr "Organizacija zaslona"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:297
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The most important part of the editor is of course the editing area, this is "
"the area where you draw your regular expression. This area is the larger "
"gray one in the middle."
msgstr ""
"Najbitniji dio urednika je naravno prostor uređivanja; to je prostor gdje Vi "
"upisujete regularne izraze.  Ovaj prostor je pretežno siv u sredini."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:301
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Above the editing area you have two Toolbars, the first one contains the "
"<link linkend=\"editingtools\">editing actions</link> - much like drawing "
"tools in a drawing program. The second Toolbar contains the <emphasis>What's "
"This?</emphasis> button, and buttons for undo and redo."
msgstr ""
"Iznad prostora za uređivanje postoje dvije alatne trake, prva sadrži <link "
"linkend=\"editingtools\">akcije editovanja</link> - skoro kao alat za "
"crtanej u programu za crtanje. Druga alatna traka sadrži dugme <emphasis>Šta "
"je ovo?</emphasis>, i dugmad za Poništi i Ponovi poništeno."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:307
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Below the editing area you find the regular expression currently build, in "
"the so called ascii syntax. The ascii syntax is updated while you edit the "
"regular expression in the graphical editor. If you rather want to update the "
"ascii syntax then please do, the graphical editor is updated on the fly to "
"reflect your changes."
msgstr ""
"Ispod prostora za uređivanje naći ćete regularni izraz trenutno napravljen, "
"u njegovom nazivu u ascii sintaksi. Ascii sintaksa se ažurira dok uređujete "
"regularne izraze u grafičkom uređivaču. Ukoliko radije želite da ažurirate "
"ascii sintaksu samo izvolite, grafički uređivač se ažurira u pokretu da bi "
"reflektovao vaše izmjene."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:314
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Finally to the left of the editor area you will find a number of pre-built "
"regular expressions. They serve two purposes: (1) When you load the editor "
"with a regular expression then this regular expression is made "
"<emphasis>nicer</emphasis> or more comprehensive by replacing common regular "
"expressions. In the screen dump above, you can see how the ascii syntax \".*"
"\" have been replaced with a box saying \"anything\". (2) When you insert "
"regular expression you may find building blocks for your own regular "
"expression from the set of pre build regular expressions. See the section on "
"<link linkend=\"userdefinedregexps\">user defined regular expressions</link> "
"to learn how to save your own regular expressions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:331
#, no-c-format
msgid "Editing Tools"
msgstr "Alati uređivanja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:332
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The text in this section expects that you have read the chapter on <link "
"linkend=\"whatIsARegExp\">what a regular expression is</link>, or have "
"previous knowledge on this subject."
msgstr ""
"Tekst ovog poglavlja očekuje da ste pročitali poglavlje na <link linkend="
"\"whatIsARegExp\">šta su regularni izrazi</link>, ili imate predznanje o "
"ovome."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:336
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All the editing tools are located in the toolbar above editing area. Each of "
"them will be described in the following."
msgstr ""
"Svi ovi alati za uređivanje se nalaze u alatnoj traci iznad prostora za "
"uređivanje. Slijedi opis svakog od njih."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:342
#, no-c-format
msgid "Selection Tool"
msgstr "Alat za odabir"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:346
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The selection tool is used to mark elements for cut-and-paste and drag-and-"
"drop. This is very similar to a selection tool in any drawing program."
msgstr ""
"Ovaj alat za odabir se koristi da označite elemente za rezanje-i-umetanje i "
"povuci-i-ispusti. Ovo je veoma slično alatima za odabir u bilo kojem "
"programu za crtanje."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:353
#, no-c-format
msgid "Text Tool"
msgstr "Alat za tekst"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:363
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using this tool you will insert normal text to match. The text is matched "
"literally, &ie; you do not have to worry about escaping of special "
"characters. In the example above the following regular expression will be "
"build: <literal>abc\\*\\\\\\)</literal>"
msgstr ""
"Korištenjem ovog alata umećete normalni tekst za podudaranje. Tekst se "
"doslovno podudara, &ie; ne morate brinuti o izostavljanju specijalnih "
"znakova. U primjeru iznad regularni izraz bi bio izgrađen kao: <literal>abc"
"\\*\\\\\\)</literal>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:371
#, no-c-format
msgid "Character Tool"
msgstr "Alat za znakove"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:379
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using this tool you insert character ranges. Examples includes what in ASCII "
"text says <literal>[0-9]</literal>, <literal>[^a-zA-Z,_]</literal>. When "
"inserting an item with this tool a dialog will appear, in which you specify "
"the character ranges."
msgstr ""
"Korištenjem ovog alata umećete rang znakova. Primjeri uključuju šta u ASCII "
"tekstu znači <literal>[0-9]</literal>, <literal>[^a-zA-Z,_]</literal>. Kada "
"umećete stavku sa ovim alatom pojavit će se dijalog, u kojem specificirate "
"rang znakova."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:385
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See description of <link linkend=\"repeatregexp\">repeated regular "
"expressions</link>."
msgstr ""
"Pogledajte objašnjenje <link linkend=\"repeatregexp\">ponovljena regularnih "
"izraza</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:391
#, no-c-format
msgid "Any Character Tool"
msgstr "Bilo koji znak Alat"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:398
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is the regular expression \"dot\" (.). It matches any single character."
msgstr ""
"Ovo je regularni izraz \"tačka\" (.). Ona se podudara sa bilo kojim znakom."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:407
#, no-c-format
msgid "Repeat Tool"
msgstr "Alat ponavljanja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:415
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is the repeated elements. This includes what in ASCII syntax is "
"represented using an asterix (*), a plus (+), a question mark (?), and "
"ranges ({3,5}). When you insert an item using this tool, a dialog will "
"appear asking for the number of times to repeat."
msgstr ""
"Ovo su elementi koji se ponavljanju. Ovo uključuje šta je u ASCII sintaksi "
"predstavljeno korištenjem asteriksa (*), plusa (+), znaka pitanja (?), i "
"rangova ({3,5}). Kada umetnete stavku koriteći ovaj alat, pojavit će se "
"dijalog koji Vas pita za broj ponavljanja koji želite."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:422
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You specify what to repeat by drawing the repeated content inside the box "
"which this tool inserts."
msgstr ""
"Vi specificirate šta želite da se ponovi ucrtavajući sadržaj unutar okvira "
"koji ovaj alat umeće."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:425
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Repeated elements can both be built from the outside in and the inside out. "
"That is you can first draw what to be repeated, select it and use the repeat "
"tool to repeat it. Alternatively you can first insert the repeat element, "
"and draw what is to be repeated inside it."
msgstr ""
"Povovljeni elementi mogu biti napravljeni i spolja i iznutra. To je da prvo "
"ucrtate šta želite da se ponavlja, odaberete to i koristite alat za "
"ponavljanje da to ponovite. Alternativno možete prvo umetnuti element za "
"ponavljanje, i ucrtati šta da se ponavlja unutar toga."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:432
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See description on the <link linkend=\"repeatregexp\">repeated regular "
"expressions</link>."
msgstr ""
"Pogledajte objašnjenje na <link linkend=\"repeatregexp\">ponavljanja "
"regularnih izraza</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:439
#, no-c-format
msgid "Alternative Tool"
msgstr "Alternativni alat"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:446
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is the alternative regular expression (|). You specify the alternatives "
"by drawing each alternative on top of each other inside the box that this "
"tool inserts."
msgstr ""
"Ovo je alternativni regularni izraz (|). Specificirate alternative "
"ucrtavajući svaku alternativu na vrh svake strane okvira koji ovaj alat "
"umeće."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:450
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See description on <link linkend=\"altnregexp\">alternative regular "
"expressions</link>"
msgstr ""
"Pogledajte objašnjenje na <link linkend=\"altnregexp\">alternativni "
"regularni izrazi</link>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:457
#, no-c-format
msgid "Compound Tool"
msgstr "Alat za sastavljanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:464
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The compound tool does not represent any regular expressions. It is used to "
"group other sub parts together in a box, which easily can be collapsed to "
"only its title. This can be seen in the right part of the screen dump above."
msgstr ""
"Alat za sastavljanje ne predstavlja ni jedan regularni izraz. Koristi se da "
"grupira druge pod dijelove zajedno u okvir, koji lako mogu biti srušeni u "
"svoj naziv. Ovo se može vidjeti u pravom dijelu zaslona smještenom iznad."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:474
#, no-c-format
msgid "Line Start/End Tools"
msgstr "Alat za početak/kraj linije"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:484
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The line start and line end tools matches the start of the line, and the end "
"of the line respectively. The regular expression in the screen dump above "
"thus matches lines only matches spaces."
msgstr ""
"Alat za početak i alat za kraj linije poredi početak linije, i kraj linije "
"respektivno. Regularni izraz u zaslonu prikazanom iznad poredi linije samo "
"poređenjem razmaka."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:489
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See description of <link linkend=\"positionregexp\">position regular "
"expressions</link>."
msgstr ""
"Pogledajte objašnjenje <link linkend=\"positionregexp\">pozicija regularnih "
"izraza</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:497
#, no-c-format
msgid "Word (Non)Boundary Tools"
msgstr "Alat za (Bez)Granične riječi"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:506
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The boundary tools matches a word boundary respectively a non-word boundary. "
"The regular expression in the screen dump thus matches any words starting "
"with <literal>the</literal>. The word <literal>the</literal> itself is, "
"however, not matched."
msgstr ""
"Alat za granice poredi granice riječi respektivno sa riječima bez granice. "
"Dakle regularni izrazi na datom zaslonu porede bilo koju riječ koja počinje "
"sa <literal>the</literal>. Riječ <literal>the</literal>, se ipak ne podudara."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:511
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See description of <link linkend=\"boundaryregexp\">boundary regular "
"expressions</link>."
msgstr ""
"Opis <link linkend=\"boundaryregexp\">granica regularnih izraza</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:519
#, no-c-format
msgid "Positive/Negative Lookahead Tools"
msgstr "Alat za Pozitivni/Negativni pregled"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:529
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The look ahead tools either specify a positive or negative regular "
"expression to match. The match is, however, not part of the total match."
msgstr ""
"Alati za pregled ili specificiraju pozitivne ili negativne regularne izraze "
"da se porede. Podudaranje, ipak, nije dio totalnog podudaranja."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:533
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note: You are only allowed to place lookaheads at the end of the regular "
"expressions. The Regular Expression Editor widget does not enforce this."
msgstr ""
"Primijetite: Dozvoljeno Vam je samo da postavite pregled na kraj regularnog "
"izraza. Regular Expression Editor programčić ne prisiljava na ovo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:537
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See description of <link linkend=\"lookaheadregexp\">look ahead regular "
"expressions</link>."
msgstr ""
"Pogledajte objašnjenje <link linkend=\"lookaheadregexp\">pregled regularnih "
"izraza</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:546
#, no-c-format
msgid "User Defined Regular Expressions"
msgstr "Korisnički Definisani Regularni Izrazi"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:547
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Located at the left of the editing area is a list box containing user "
"defined regular expressions. Some regular expressions are pre-installed with "
"your &kde; installation, while others you can save yourself."
msgstr ""
"Locirani lijevo od prostora za uređivanje je lista koja sadrži korisnički "
"definirane regularne izraze. Neki regularni izrazi su prethodno instalirani "
"sa Vašom &kde; instalacijom, dok druge možete sami sačuvati."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:552
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These regular expression serves two purposes (<link linkend="
"\"screenorganization\">see detailed description</link>), namely (1) to offer "
"you a set of building block and (2) to make common regular expressions "
"prettier."
msgstr ""
"Ovi regularni izrazi imaju dvije svrhe (<link linkend=\"screenorganization"
"\">pogledajte detaljno objašnjenje</link>), naime (1) da ponute set blokova "
"za izgradnju (2) da učine zajedničke regularne izraze ljepšim."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:557
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can save your own regular expressions by right clicking the mouse button "
"in the editing area, and choosing <literal>Save Regular Expression</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Možete sačuvati Vaš vlastiti regularni izraz desnim klikom na miša na dugme "
"u prostoru za uređivanje, odabirom <literal>Sačuvaj regularni izraz</"
"literal>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:561
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the regular expression you save is within a <link linkend=\"compoundtool"
"\">compound container</link> then the regular expression will take part in "
"making subsequent regular expressions prettier."
msgstr ""
"Ukoliko je regularni izraz koji ste sačuvali unutar <link linkend="
"\"compoundtool\">skladišta spajanja</link> tada će regularni izrazi uzeti "
"zasluge za pravljenje sljedećih regularnih izraza ljepšim."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:566
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"User defined regular expressions can be deleted or renamed by pressing the "
"right mouse button on top of the regular expression in question in the list "
"box."
msgstr ""
"Korisnički definirani regularni izrazi mogu biti izbrisani ili preimenovani "
"pritiskom desnog dugmeta miša na vrh regularnih izraza u pitanju na listi."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:576
#, no-c-format
msgid "Reporting bugs and Suggesting Features"
msgstr "Prijave bagova i predlaganje opcija"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:577
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Bug reports and feature requests should be submitted through the <ulink url="
"\"http://bugs.kde.org/\">&kde; Bug Tracking System</ulink>. <emphasis role="
"\"strong\">Before</emphasis> you report a bug or suggest a feature, please "
"check that it hasn't already been <ulink url=\"http://bugs.kde.org/buglist."
"cgi?quicksearch=kregexpeditor\">reported/suggested.</ulink>"
msgstr ""
"Prijave bagova i zahtjevi za opcije mogu biti poslani kroz <ulink url="
"\"http://bugs.kde.org/\">&kde; Bug Tracking System</ulink>. <emphasis role="
"\"strong\">Prije</emphasis> nego prijavite bag ili pregložite opciju, molimo "
"da provjerite da već ne postoji <ulink url=\"http://bugs.kde.org/buglist.cgi?"
"quicksearch=kregexpeditor\">reported/suggested.</ulink>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:588
#, no-c-format
msgid "Frequently Asked Questions"
msgstr "Često postavljena pitanja"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:590
#, no-c-format
msgid "Does the regular expression editor support back references?"
msgstr "Da li regularni izrazi podržavaju povratne reference?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:591
#, no-c-format
msgid "No currently this is not supported. It is planned for the next version."
msgstr "Ovo trenutno nije podržano. Planirano je za sljedeću verziju."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:596
#, no-c-format
msgid "Does the regular expression editor support showing matches?"
msgstr "Da li uređivač regularnih izraza podržava prikaz podudaranja?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:597
#, no-c-format
msgid "No, hopefully this will be available in the next version."
msgstr "Ne, nadamo se da će biti podržano u sljedećoj verziji."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:601
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"I'm the author of a &kde; program, how can I use this widget in my "
"application?"
msgstr ""
"Ja sam autor &kde; programa, kako da koristim programčić u svojoj aplikaciji?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:603
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See <ulink url=\"http://developer.kde.org/documentation/library/cvs-api/"
"classref/interfaces/KRegExpEditorInterface.html\">The documentation for the "
"class KRegExpEditorInterface</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Pogledajte <ulink url=\"http://developer.kde.org/documentation/library/cvs-"
"api/classref/interfaces/KRegExpEditorInterface.html\">The documentation for "
"the class KRegExpEditorInterface</ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:608
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"I cannot find the <emphasis>Edit Regular expression</emphasis> button in for "
"example konqueror on another KDE3 installation, why?"
msgstr ""
"Ne mogu pronaći dugme <emphasis>Uredi Regularne izraze</emphasis> u "
"primjeru  konqueror ili drugoj KDE3 instalaciji, zašto?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:610
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The regular expression widget is located in the package &kde;-utils. If you "
"do not have this package installed, then the <emphasis>edit regular "
"expressions</emphasis> buttons will not appear in the programs."
msgstr ""
"Programčić regularnih izraza je lociran u paketu &kde;-utils. Ukoliko nemate "
"ovaj paket instaliran, tada se dugme <emphasis>uredi regularne izraze</"
"emphasis> neće pojaviti u programima."

